<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="780" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/639.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Messrs. <gloss type="from">Kuhn, Loeb and
                                    Company</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>We have the honor to acknowledge receipt of your telegram in reference to
                            Liberia and we shall at once take up the question which you bring to our
                            attention with the fiscal agency and the attorneys and advise you as
                            promptly as possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuhn, Loeb and Company.</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>